data.meta_description:
79 likes, 2 comments - ajcnews on March 10, 2024: "Usher Raymond IV was born in Dallas, Texas and grew up in Chattanooga, Tennessee, before moving to Atlanta with his mother and brother at 12.

When he was 15, he signed with LaFace Records, which released his self-titled debut album in 1994. Over the course of the next 30 years, Usher solidified his position as one of the greatest entertainers in pop music.

As an eight-time Grammy winner, @usher is considered the male R&B superstar of our time.

Read the full story at the link in our bio.".
